laboratory_examinations.findings: The left kidney is subtly hypoenhancing compared to the right kidney with cortical scarring along the upper pole. Multiple subcentimeter cysts/cystic change noted in the lower pole. Appendicolith is seen at the base of the appendix, which is dilated, demonstrating mural edema, measuring up to 1.3 cm. Adjacent fat stranding is present without discrete fluid collection or extraluminal air. These findings are compatible with acute uncomplicated appendicitis.
